Implement: $ARGUMENTS

## Before You Code (MANDATORY)

1. Read @memory/INDEX.md (global overview)
2. Read @memory/conventions.md (project patterns)
3. Read @memory/workflows/auth/insights.md (auth learnings)
4. Read @memory/workflows/auth/gotchas.md (auth traps)
5. Read @memory/workflows/auth/test-flows.md (existing test commands)

## Loop (strict order, no skipping)

1. **Plan**: Outline auth scope based on insights read above.
   - Auth method? (JWT, session, OAuth)
   - Providers? (local, Google, GitHub)
   - MFA required?

2. **Code**: Implement following conventions.md.
   - User model (if new)
   - Auth service
   - Middleware/guards
   - Login/logout/register routes

3. **Migrate**: If DB changes → delegate `@agents/migrator`.
   - User table
   - Session/token storage

4. **Unit Test**: Delegate `@agents/tester`.
   - Test auth functions
   - FAIL → fix, re-run. Max 3 attempts.

5. **Integration**: Run integration tests.
   - Full auth flow
   - Same fix loop.

6. **E2E**: Delegate `@agents/e2e-runner` with test-flows.md commands.
   - Browser-based auth flow
   - Same fix loop.

7. **Review**: Delegate `@agents/reviewer`.
   - Security focus
   - Address findings.

## After Shipping (MANDATORY)

1. Update @memory/workflows/auth/insights.md (what learned)
2. Update @memory/workflows/auth/gotchas.md (new traps found)
3. Update @memory/workflows/auth/test-flows.md (new test commands)
4. Create @memory/decisions/auth/{{date}}-slug.md (ADR)
5. If global insight → append to @memory/INDEX.md
6. **Report**: Summarize shipped, decisions, insights captured.

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Passwords hashed (bcrypt/argon2)
- [ ] Tokens have expiry
- [ ] CSRF protection
- [ ] Rate limiting on login
- [ ] Secure cookie flags
